Russia
In the legislation of the Russian Federation, there is no definition of the concept of loitering or related in meaning. Therefore, there is no responsibility for such acts. Any citizen can freely and arbitrarily long be in public places. However, in the Russian Federation there are certain zones established by law, in which persons without a clearly defined purpose is prohibited. These include, for example, traffic safety zones (bridges, exclusion zones of railways and motorways, the edge of the platform of subway stations marked with a marking line, etc.